Iranian students are ready to die for their country's nuclear program.
They created a human shield
A few hundred college students created a human shield around a nuclear site in Iran.
They want to support their country's nuclear programme in the face of a possible Israeli attack.
The students began to pray at noon in front of the site and then wished for the death of the EU and Israel.
A few hundred students from Ispahan universities created a human shield on Tuesday around the nuclear technology centre in Ispahan where uranium is transformed.
They openly expressed that they would defend their country's nuclear program at the risk of their own lives.
The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) has noted in its latest information that Iran has continued to strengthen its nuclear weapons.
