The need for speed Run is fighting all over America.
Revision
Originally a problem-free race is transformed because of a set of stupid mistakes of people who have nothing to do with it in a routine morning shift to work.
It fulfils everyone's ambition to some extent, but it is of no use if no one wants to do anything more.
The new subtitled game The Run produced great expectations before it was released.
He promised to take a new direction with the already old Need for Speed racing series and to release a kind of game from playable games that would not only count with points.
So we were curious how the added passages will be when the main hero comes out of his car and does what he wants.
As is already the case in the NFS series, the result is completely different than what was expected.
These are potentially arcade racing games but the whole shoots down because of some useless mistakes that have already existed for several years.
These are not really mistakes but rather the expression of incomprehensible lazyness on the part of developers.
The adventure begins very well.
You're caught up in the adventure of which the main hero Jack has character problems and to solve them begins to participate in illegal races across America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco and your mission is to arrive first in New York.
The idea has some interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than 50 races.
The result is that each race takes place on another route and the planned stages in different environments that distinguish themselves quite well from each other and are interesting.
The player does not have the feeling for a moment that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are of quite nice increase even if the graphic technical level is of the same type as the previous series.
I mean, it's not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in highly snowy mountains is very pleasant visually.
The tests are in addition to times enhanced by an unusual element.
For example, in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly reduces your visibility.
Then in the mountains you have to be careful that an avalanche does not fall on you.
Next to this, the different races are well arranged behind each other.
There are only a few, but that is enough.
Moments ago you try to surpass the requested number of opponents (as in a classic race) then you run against the watch (classic fuel with the chronometer) and then wait for another duel with an opponent.
From time to time you also have the police who enter the game and who are trying to make the situation upside down.
The novelty is the out-of-vehicle passages.
Rather, it's an interactive animation when most of the time Jack runs away in front of someone and you have to help him by typing on the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
What is surprising is that there are fewer moments of this type than you expect (to be concrete there are only three).
The result is this because this element is not likely to interfere and is placed, in the context described above, in the elements that enhance the game.
The driving model is in the tradition of previous games.
Which means that at present there is nothing extraordinary but it cannot be said that it is negative.
As far as realistic simulation is concerned, you will have to look elsewhere.
But although one can find better in the competition the driving model goes very well with the type of design of the races.
So everything's okay.
The problems begin to appear after a while.
The difference between the driving model and the collisions is not yet complete.
We do not expect this game to be complicated deformation and collisions, but when you do not have any idea of how your car behaves during a collision with any object, it is not completely good.
During tight exceedances you sometimes touch each other slightly but otherwise your car leaves in crazy voltiges.
Or it's crumbled.
Thanks to the restart system this is not really a problem but it really irritates you.
The restart is done so that when you broke the figure or you went out in the decor the game brings you back to the last point on the route.
But you only have 5 restarts.
When you have used the 5 restarts you have to start the game again from the beginning.
So it's more a tool, in case something doesn't happen properly, than something you can really rely on.
Sometimes the restarts do not help and the solution must be found by remembering the piece of route in question.
The big hit of this game is that the same actions are found in the same places.
For example, there are some turns that need to be passed in a certain way, otherwise it doesn't pass.
Otherwise you meet on a given location "civilian" vehicles always in the same configuration as you arrived first, fifth, 5 seconds in advance or one minute late.
What makes you angry are the situations when you see the opponent easily passing between two cars coming in the opposite direction and when you arrive, you either have to stand aside and convert them or brake them.
It's equal if you go to meet him because it's "calculated" in such a way that for the given situation it always happens close to your nose.
Opponents still have other advantages.
All the time in the game, you, you arrive in some places, again without worrying about time, and you still have the same opponent that precedes you in the same place.
This gets the most angry at the end of the game when you're riding on a long bridge in the opposite direction.
The adversary must at all costs pass before you.
When it passes in front of you it hides the sight of other vehicles in the opposite direction and you collide many times.
One can understand that the purpose of this game is to do something captivating and full of adrenaline, but it is clear that you get bored quickly.
And that's too bad because through a simple driving model the game is interesting and places with so much action that you don't have time to follow everything that's going on.
And it's equal if it's because of the concept of 50 unique routes, that the order of races is such that there's no chance of getting bored or something else.
The original idea is to change the car during the races.
You have to pay attention to the petrol pumps on the routes because you can change car there however most of the time the one you have enough.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, big American cylinders for straight highways and super sports cars with exotic auras on very technical pipes for example on yaw roads in the mountains.
And the mode of challenges, which are races in particular places that you know of adventure, goes very well with the main diet of history.
You receive not only medals but also experience points that add to your profile that is common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest level of driver, different objects start unlocking:
It connects on-line with the Autolog function which inter alia compares your results with those of other players and provides you with other functions in the community.
One of the most difficult blows to understand is the situation of the last race of the adventure.
You arrive with your car in the subway tunnel (it looks like) where you drive in the dark on the tracks (it looks like).
Your speed indicator tells you between 150 and 200 km/hour (a priori) and behind you comes a metro train which sends you the car directly to scrap metal.
At the editorial board we had a discussion for a few days about whether someone really thought out when creating this game or whether the authors really think we're idiots.
The technical part of the game is not extra, but the visual part is usually pleasant and in some cases really great.
What's bothering is that in more extreme situations, imaging doesn't hold the level and in some cases tragically.
This mainly concerns accidents with a large number of participants when fluid imaging is no longer useful for you.
The sound part is good and the track is of choice.
In order to please as many as possible and especially the young audience a new soundtrack was created in the style "I mix everything", but one can expect that no one will buy the game for music.
General Impression of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore really confused.
If the game didn't have these stupid mistakes we could say without fear that this is the best NFS production in recent years.
But this game gives the impression of not being finished.
The fun is really good but prepare for the mistakes to hit you in the eyes with the strength of an airfield reflector.
The Velvet students in concert with the choirs of Charles University
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivities that link the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs from higher schools and secondary classes.
The highlight of the festival is two concerts on 17 November.
"Charles University has an important part in this festival."
"Among the choirs there is the Choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the committee of the festival sits the rector Vaclav Hampl," says the head of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the concert of the Choir of high schools and secondary classes which takes place with free entry on November 17 from 2 p.m. on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
On the program there is the composition of well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening the concert "Velvet students" takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady, during which the choirs of the higher schools as well as that of Charles University take place.
The aim of the Festa Academica is not only to celebrate with dignity the International Student Day and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present to the public a chorus music of the highest level and to develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organiser is the Czech Cheers Union in cooperation with the Jan Kepler High School.
All the action is under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, msical meetings, student happenings and other activities.
Interested parties can find all the information on the festival's web pages www.festaaacademica.cz.
Vicenova, Ambassador to the European Union:
Czechs behave like negativists and Eurosceptics
"The Lisbon Treaty has radically removed the balance between the institutions"
"I didn't expect such a hard war."
"It will last 5.6 years before the situation calms down and all players get used to their new role", that is how Milena Vicenova began her presentation at the Faculty of Law the Czech Ambassador to the European Union.
When she managed to describe the various bodies of the EU and their relations in such a comprehensible and visible way, to the point that a large number of lecturers from the Faculty of Law at Charles University could envy her, she showed how seriously she takes her motto "understandable and openly about Europe".
Mrs Vicenova paid tribute to the work of Herman Van Rompuye, the new permanent President of the European Council.
"From the beginning, the criticisms that he is bland, that he is a round-the-cook, that he cannot replace any mission and I must say that he has cut off everyone's breath because he holds his role to perfection."
"He is a man who knows how to listen to 27 member states, communicate well with them and has a clear vision of the direction to take from Europe".
She explained the new post of the High Representative for Foreign Affairs and Defence Policy as part of an answer to the question: "Who is the European Union?" "What telephone number should I call?", therefore as an important step towards uniqueness and greater readability of the Union's policy vis-à-vis states, such as China or India.
No one wants to ban our syrecky (cooked cheese that smells very loud)
Mrs Vicenova also referred to the agenda that has lived, lives and will live in the European Council in a near time.
She called the Czech Presidency two years ago a success.
The Czechs have resolved the rising financial crisis, the gas crisis or have organized an Eastern Partnership Summit.
It described the fall of the government as very negative and damaged the image of the Czech Republic.
Czech representation in the EU is currently very busy.
In the words of Mrs L'Ambassador, "the activity has beaten its fullness" not only for the Presidency but also for the financial crisis which continues to be resolved now.
We must also approve the Union's new septimal budget, which is becoming very complicated because of the current economic situation.
As it would appear that the budget will be thin and with a view to savings, which branch will have priority, which countries will be assisted the most, the least, everything is to be resolved in the context of future negotiations.
The Ambassador recalled her slogans with which she arrived in Brussels "For an understandable Europe".
"I really don't like abbreviations, foreign words, jargons that nobody understands.
As the citizen must understand, it is true that in Brussels no one makes round or twisted pickles, bananas differently large or that no one has forbidden us to make syrecky."
It wants to make better use of the EU's environment and to see more Czechs in the European institutions.
A multi-speed Europe awaits us
According to Ambassador Czechs have the reputation of being Eurosceptics and people who see things only in their negative aspect more than positively.
Moreover, she is sorry to see such a small Czech representation in the European institutions.
The fault, in her view, results from several factors, such as the timidity of our candidates, their inability to write a letter of motivation and weak support from the Czech side.
In addition to a successful Czech presidency, she then stressed the strength and cooperation of the Visegrad Group.
"Believe me, when the Pole, the Magyar, the Slovak come to me, this Frenchman says to me: 'Hey, what are you doing there, what is this Visegrad group still doing?" and he is not at all happy."
According to Mrs Vicenova, in the near future it is tough new rules on budgetary policy that are waiting for the Member States.
It is the concept of a two-speed Europe, if not at several speeds, that prevails rather than a "new European Federation".
"We have countries in the euro area and others outside the area."
"We have the Schengen area, we also have the Institute for Enhanced Cooperation".
In the first place it was said that cooperation between countries that want it and those that do not want it remain in their corner."
"There will be many such institutes and there will be a truly two-speed Europe," Ms Vicenova expects.
From this point of view, it also appreciated the mission of the Czech Republic and Herman Van Rompuye to determine the basis on which all issues with an impact on the EU should be discussed among all EU members and not just the members of the Eurozone.
