The basis for this long-term strategy was laid by the firm's first chief, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He left the slogan that many global problems can be solved if people are willing to think.
His slogan "PENSE"!" has become the imprint around which the life of a future giant will develop (and also the title of the internal magazine that IBM began to publish in 1935).
This was the basis of the company's culture carefully developed by Watson.
For us IBM means a long-term thought of continuous movements directed towards the future.
IBM has survived a hundred years thanks to the fact that it still remains faithful to its core values and yet was not afraid to change all the others around it.
This has allowed us in our first century to transform technology, business and society.
We hope that in the second century we will reach even more" the current director of the firm Samuel J. Palmisano has delaid for the anniversary.
A well-prepared system
Watson, in the thirties, began to take care of his employees like Bata in the Czech Republic - IBM's people were the only among the first American employees to have paid vacations, an insurance paid by the employer plus an elegant employee uniform and a well-developed system of rewards for inventors and merchants.
In the same way IBM has a well-developed customer relationship system.
The company was at first great in the discovery of talent- as one of the first firms to have abolished any form of discrimination and thus had the choice.
The current plan is completely in the spirit of the anti-discrimination strategy since it will be a woman- Virginia Rometty - who should replace Palmisano at the head of IBM.
She has been with IBM for 30 years and is currently Head of Sales, Marketing and Strategy.
IBM in recent years has been doing what is called jamy, brain-storming online from which many future strategies and innovations have emerged.
It is not surprising that he has a lot of ideas - in the firm there are almost 500,000 people who work.
