The arrangements adopted by the Austrian Government are close to the "German model", with Germany being the first European country to adopt such a "rule".
By 2017, the structural government deficit will have to decrease by 0.75% of gross domestic product (GDP) each year and, starting in 2017, the federal government's structural government deficit will not have to exceed 0.35% of GDP each year, while regional states and municipalities will have to submit balanced budgets.
The objective is to bring public debt up to the 60% criterion laid down in the Maastricht Treaty by 2020/21.
